{"id": "1406285155013886044", "channel_id": "1406285155013886044", "type": 0, "author_id": "302004389927845889", "author_name": "darkfeet", "author_bot": false, "content": "As the title suggests, application of the discount after acquiring 1st Tawil's enlightenment isn't functioning correctly (isn't applied), notably in the environment without interference of external factors. (Examples: 1 to 4 and 7)\n\nIn Addition the computation of the cost, assuming following external factors: \"Symptom card: Delirium\" and \"Delirium Cage\" (And the intention which sets cost to 3) - is calculated incorrectly. While the discount usually is applied, the final cost of the Omniscient Verity is quite hard to believe to be correct. (Examples: 5, 6 and 8)\n\n(While the following examples wont show the interaction with Symptom Card delirium as the probability of it aligning isn't particularly high, i would like to still bring it up and specify that the algorithm of calculating the cost in that interaction is identical to the stated interaction with Delirium Cage (That would be example 9, but it doesn't capture all the nuances at that moment, but i hope it's still enough to point out that the bug does persist in that interaction))\n\nBelow i will list some of the examples i have captured, but outside of these examples this bug happens quite frequently:", "timestamp": "2025-08-16T14:35:08.470000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2025-08-17T01:08:07.606000+00:00", "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "👍", "emoji_id": null, "count": 5}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1406285155013886044", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "💭「Processing」Tawil, Inconsistent 1 Arithemetica discount application on Omniscient Verity (Skill 1)", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "thread_tags": ["1361168893200044183"]}
